<h2><I>CGAL::is_ccw_strongly_convex_2</I></h2>

  
 
     
<A NAME="Index_anchor_526"></A> 
 
   

   
     
     
<A NAME="Index_anchor_527"></A> 

   


   
     
     
<A NAME="Index_anchor_528"></A>
<P>

<H3>Definition</H3>
<P>

The function <I><A HREF="Function_is_ccw_strongly_convex_2.html#Cross_link_anchor_622">is_ccw_strongly_convex_2</A></I> determines if a given sequence of points defines
a counterclockwise-oriented, stongly convex polygon.  
A set of points is said to be strongly convex 
if it consists of only extreme points
(<I>i.e.</I>, vertices of the convex hull).
<P>

<I>#include &lt;<A HREF="../../../include/CGAL/convexity_check_2.h">CGAL/convexity_check_2.h</A>&gt;</I>
<P>

